$interpreted: Pang: Don't be angry... I'm sure the elders refused your plans for revolution with good reason.
Yao: Hmph! They have no reason other than corruption! They've bought into the Alliance's greed!
Pang: Well, the Tiger Tribe is part of the Alliance...
Yao: Not you too, Pang!? Don't buy into their lies! The Alliance cares about nothing but protecting their own interests!
Yao: Hmph... Now it seems I have no other choice...
Pang: Yao!? Yao, you can't!! You will tear the Alliance apart!
Yao: How else can I keep these sheep from waltzing off to slaughter?
Pang: Ugh...
Yu: Prince Yao, I have something to report.
Pang: General Yu.
Yao: What is it?
Yu: The elders feel you've taken on too much stress lately, and you've neglected your health. They have invited you to a feast in three days time.
Yao: And they have a general acting as their messenger boy, now? Do you not feel undervalued?
Yu: ...I am simply following orders.
Yao: Hmph... Tell them I'll be there.
Yu: Yes, Prince Yao.
Pang: Yao... General Yu is a respected member of this tribe. I fear you were quite rude to him just now.
Yao: So? All that general wants is to rise the ranks like all the other sheep. Why show him any respect?
Pang: I do not see him that way.
Yao: Pang, with circumstances as precarious as they are, I cannot trust anyone out of my immediate circle...
Joo-Won: *Cough* *Cough*~ Gyagh! Almost didn't make it out!
Yao: Trying to take us down with you, hmm?
Scared Girl: W-Wait, my hands were tied! I had to join the Bloodfangs if I wanted to stay alive!!
Yao: That's what they all say.
Yao: Now, tell me everything you know!
Scared Girl: Gyagh... Our leader knew there was someone chasing him... for a while now... so he sent me here to ambush you.
Yao: Keep talking.
Scared Girl: I-I know where our leader is... I'll tell you, if you spare my life.
Yao: You're just some kid, why would you know where he is?
Scared Girl: S-Sometimes I deliver c-correspondence, so I know where... he is...
Yao: Hm...
Joo-Won: Hey, why not just let her go? She is of more use to us alive, if what she says is true.
Yao: That's a big "if". Dogs like her say whatever they can to keep their lives.
Joo-Won: That may be so, but we need a new lead.
Joo-Won: Give people a chance, they might surprise you.
Yao: I've already had enough surprises.
Yao: Eh? Another ambush?
Bloodfang Killer: Kill them all!!
Yao: They're really rolling out the red carpet.
Joo-Won: Hmph... gyagh...
Scared Girl: Help me!!
Scared Girl: Wait, I'm a Bloodfang, too!
Bloodfang Killer: Shut up!
Joo-Won: Get away from her!
Joo-Won: Are you okay?
Joo-Won: Thank you for helping me, otherwise I would be done for.
Scared Girl: No, no, I should be thanking you!
Joo-Won: You... killed them all...
Yao: Not all of them... not yet.
Joo-Won: Wait, Night Wanderer...
Joo-Won: She helped me!
Scared Girl: D-Don't... please...
Scared Girl: Please, oh hero, come help me! He's trying to kill me!!
Joo-Won: Night Wanderer, you saw that she just saved me. Can you not simply give her a chance?
Yao: Tell me where your leader is.
Scared Girl: Okay, okay, I'll tell you.
Joo-Won: You're not going right now, are you?
Yao: Of course I am.
Joo-Won: But we just used so much of our energy. We should rest!
Joo-Won: And we can't bring her with us, we'll need to find somewhere to put her.
Scared Girl: This hero is right, they would kill me for sure!
Joo-Won: I know somewhere suitable just nearby.
Yao: Lead the way.
Yao: This is...
Joo-Won: My home—Ripple Village.
Yao: Ripple Village?
Joo-Won's Wife: Honey, you're home!
Joo-Won's Wife: Oh, honey, you've brought friends home again without letting me know first!
Scared Girl: There are beasts from so many different tribes here...
Joo-Won's Wife: Surprising, isn't it? My husband often brings folks back to Ripple Village who have nowhere else to go.
Joo-Won's Wife: They end up calling it home after a while.
Joo-Won: That's why everyone gets along so well here.
Yao: Why go out and about like some hero when you have a wife and a village?
Joo-Won: Don't worry, Ripple Village is hidden away, no one knows of its existence.
Joo-Won's Wife: And myself, along with the rest of the villagers, all approve of and support my husband's mission.
Yao: They all support him...
Joo-Won: Anyway, this is where we'll rest tonight! Honey, could you prepare a room for them?
Yao: No need, I will sleep outside the village.
Joo-Won: Can you not simply relax for one night? I insist!
Yao: Why? What is your aim?
Joo-Won: I aim to make sure you don't set off to fight tired and on an empty stomach.
Joo-Won: What? Are you afraid I will poison your food?
Yao: Hmph... Jokes...
Joo-Won: Remember when I said you don't understand where my belief stems from? Well it stems from here... Ripple Village.
Yao: Then you must protect it, instead of making more enemies.
Joo-Won: Are you saying I should change my methods? Maybe I should try to join the Martial Arts Tournament?
Yao: That dog and pony show? That facade only creates more sheep.
Joo-Won: I merely said that in jest, and yet... You really do not trust humanity, do you?
Yao: No, I do not. And you wouldn't either, were you to see true evil.
Joo-Won: Does this mistrust have something to do with those shackles of yours?
Yao: ...We leave at daybreak.
